Japanese reactionaries' moves for overseas aggression
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 23 (KCNA) -- Newspapers here today carry commentaries denouncing the Japanese reactionaries' moves for overseas aggression.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Japan's ruling quarters have revealed their intention to retrogressively revise the existing constitution with "bills on emergencies in areas surrounding Japan" passed through the house of representatives as an occasion, so as to gratify the design of overseas aggression, Rodong Sinmun notes, and says:   The "bills" are aimed at guaranteeing by law the wartime system and participation in military action of Japan for implementing the aggressive "Guidelines for Japan-U.S. Defence Cooperation."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The ruling quarters of Japan have so far advocated "peaceful nature" and mission of the constitution, describing Japan as a "peaceful state," and stated it would not conduct nor take part in any military actions.   However, they are now legalizing overseas aggression, throwing away the deceptive signboard of "peace."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They seek to retrogressively revise the present constitution, which bans possession of combat armed forces, and the right of belligerency and right to military action, and thus drastically increase the combat capabilities of the "Self-Defense Forces" and conduct aggressive military actions in any areas outside Japan.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   With the new "guidelines" and bills related to it, the Japanese reactionaries have expanded the sphere of Japan's "right to security" and military action into the Asia-Pacific region and legalized the "SDF's" overseas actions. 
This is a prelude to their scenario on overseas aggression.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Japan tries to repeat its past history in which it invaded Korea and other Asian countries and committed monstrous massacre and plunder.
   The Asian people should heighten vigilance against the Japanese reactionaries' overseas aggressive moves and check and frustrate them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Minju Joson says the Japanese reactionaries should stop such moves for overseas aggression at once, mindful that they will lead to their self-destruction.
